prompt:
[Verse]
The keys are crying in the dark tonight
Each note a tear a fading light
Shadows stretch long but the moon won’t fight

[Prechorus]
I chase the silence it slips through my hand
A whisper falls like a grain of sand

[Chorus]
Whispers in the rain calling my name
Soft and slow they come and go
Whispers in the rain never the same
Falling deep where no one knows

[Verse 2]
Clouds are heavy like my mind’s regret
A storm inside I can't forget
Footsteps vanish where the ground is wet

[Prechorus]
The wind it hums a broken tune
A melody carved by the silver moon

[Chorus]
Whispers in the rain calling my name
Soft and slow they come and go
Whispers in the rain never the same
Falling deep where no one knows
tags: emotional, piano-driven, minimalistic with soft dynamics and heartfelt delivery, beautiful
title: Whispers in the Rain

prompt:
[Verse]
A window cries under the silver moon
Lonely shadows stretch across my room
The clock ticks slow but the silence booms

[Chorus]
Whispers in the rain they call my name
Soft and steady they sound the same
Drip drop drip it drowns the pain
Oh whispers in the rain

[Verse 2]
Footsteps echo down an empty street
Each one a heartbeat I cannot meet
The cold bites sharp but the tears bring heat

[Prechorus]
I reach I reach but it fades away
The whispers stay the whispers stay

[Chorus]
Whispers in the rain they call my name
Soft and steady they sound the same
Drip drop drip it drowns the pain
Oh whispers in the rain

[Bridge]
The sky it weeps for all we’ve lost
Every tear a love that paid its cost
And in the puddles reflections tossed
tags: emotional, piano-driven with delicate arpeggios and swelling dynamics, soft, beautiful
title: Whispers in the Rain
